text: Edoardo Alaimo (8 January 1893 - 13 March 1962) was an Italian fencer. He competed in three events at the 1912 Summer Olympics in Stockholm, Sweden. ==References== Category:1893 births Category:1962 deaths Category:Italian male fencers Category:Olympic fencers of Italy Category:Fencers at the 1912 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Palermo
